leads.lead_text: Leaves less than 1.5 cm long, about as long as broad, with 2–3 (rarely 1 or 4) teeth on each side of lamina; known only from Otway Range and Wilsons Promontory
Leaves (when mature) 1.5–6.0 cm long, always longer than broad, with 4–6 (rarely 3) teeth on each side of lamina
